===Verb===
{{head|en|verb|head=[[answer]] for}}

# {{context|transitive}} To be held [[responsible]] for.
#: ''The mayor has a lot to '''answer for'''.''
#*{{quote-journal|year=2007|date=September|volume=197|issue=6|page=26|title=The Faculty 'Problem'|author=Wilson D Miscamble|journal=America|passage=Duffy dared to think that Queen Elizabeth I has a few things '''for''' which to '''answer'''}}
# {{context|transitive}} To [[guarantee]].
#: ''I will '''answer for''' his debt, if he can't pay on the day.''

====Usage notes====
* The verb and particle are usually not separated.

